def: A handsome Asiatic tree (Melia azedarach), common in thesouthern United States; -- called also, Pride of India, Pride ofChina, and Bead tree.
Wine boiled and mingled with honey.
A moment; an instant; as, I will be ready in a jiffy. [Colloq.]J. & H. Smith.

In a wonderful or surprising manner or degree; wonderfully.For sylphs, yet mindful of their ancient race, Are, as when women,wondrous fond of place. Pope.And now there came both mist and snow, And it grew wondrous cold.Coleridge.
Having the right form. Orthomorphic projection, a projection inwhich the angles in the figure to be projected are equal to thecorresponding angles in the projected figure.
Of a yellowish or redish brown color; as, a sorrel horse.
A genus of leguminous plants; the Kentucky coffee tree. Theleaves are cathartic, and the seeds a substitute for coffee.
A remitting; a giving up; surrender; as, the remittal of thefirst fruits. Swift.
A mature female fish.The barbel, for the preservation or their seed, both the spawner andthe milter, cover their spawn with sand. Walton.
Extended or drawn out; subjected to tension. "A highlytensioned string." Tyndall.
